John William Warner1

M, #334431, b. 18 February 1927

Last Edited=4 Feb 2009

John Warner 1

John William Warner was born on 18 February 1927.1 He married, firstly, Catherine Mellon, daughter of Paul Mellon and Mary Conover, in 1967.1 He and Catherine Mellon were divorced in 1973.1 He married, secondly, Elizabeth Rosemond Taylor, daughter of Francis Lenn Taylor and Sara Viola Warmbrodt, on 4 December 1976.1 He and Elizabeth Rosemond Taylor were divorced on 7 November 1982.1 He married, thirdly, Jeanne (?) on 15 December 2003.1

He gained the rank of Petty Officer in 1945 in the U.S. Navy.1 He fought in the Second World War in 1945.1 He graduated from Washington and Lee University, Lexington, Virginia, U.S.A. , in 1949.1 He gained the rank of Captain in 1950 in the 1st Marine Aircraft Wing, U.S. Marines.1 He fought in the Korean War between 1950 and 1953.1 He graduated from University of Virginia Law School, Virginia, U.S.A. , in 1953 with a law degree.1 He held the office of U.S. Secretary of the Navy between 1972 and 1974.1 He held the office of Member of the House of Representatives [U.S.] between 1979 and 2009, from Virginia.1

Margaret Leighton1

F, #334438, b. 26 February 1922, d. 13 January 1976

Last Edited=3 Feb 2009

Margaret Leighton was born on 26 February 1922 at Barnt Green, Worcestershire, England .1 She married, firstly, Max Reinhardt in 1947.1 She and Max Reinhardt were divorced in 1955.1 She married, secondly, Laurence Harvey in 1957.1 She and Laurence Harvey were divorced in 1961.1 She married, thirdly, Michael Wilding in 1964.1 She died on 13 January 1976 at age 53 at Chichester, Sussex, England , from multiple slerosis, without issue.1

She was a stage and film actress.1
